{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":968,"text":"Chris Anderson: Welcome\nto this next edition of TED Dialogues."},{"time":5604,"text":"We're trying to do\nsome bridging here today."},{"time":8694,"text":"You know, the American dream\nhas inspired millions of people"},{"time":11638,"text":"around the world for many years."},{"time":14937,"text":"Today, I think, you can say\nthat America is divided,"},{"time":20678,"text":"perhaps more than ever,"},{"time":22363,"text":"and the divisions seem\nto be getting worse."},{"time":24442,"text":"It's actually really hard\nfor people on different sides"},{"time":28307,"text":"to even have a conversation."},{"time":29785,"text":"People almost feel..."},{"time":32121,"text":"disgusted with each other."},{"time":34648,"text":"Some families can't even speak\nto each other right now."},{"time":39681,"text":"Our purpose in this dialogue today\nis to try to do something about that,"},{"time":44253,"text":"to try to have a different kind\nof conversation,"},{"time":46937,"text":"to do some listening, some thinking,\nsome understanding."},{"time":51202,"text":"And I have two people with us\nto help us do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54654,"text":"They're not going to come at this\nhammer and tong against each other."},{"time":57917,"text":"This is not like cable news."},{"time":59705,"text":"This is two people who have both spent\na lot of their working life"},{"time":65222,"text":"in the political center\nor right of the center."},{"time":67533,"text":"They've immersed themselves\nin conservative worldviews, if you like."},{"time":71521,"text":"They know that space very well."},{"time":73668,"text":"And we're going to explore together"},{"time":75401,"text":"how to think about\nwhat is happening right now,"},{"time":78446,"text":"and whether we can find new ways to bridge"},{"time":81615,"text":"and just to have wiser,\nmore connected conversations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84856,"text":"With me, first of all, Gretchen Carlson,"},{"time":87983,"text":"who has spent a decade\nworking at Fox News,"},{"time":93297,"text":"hosting \"Fox and Friends\"\nand then \"The Real Story,\""},{"time":97799,"text":"before taking a courageous stance\nin filing sexual harassment claims"},{"time":103596,"text":"against Roger Ailes,"},{"time":104836,"text":"which eventually led\nto his departure from Fox News."},{"time":108662,"text":"David Brooks, who has earned the wrath"},{"time":111489,"text":"of many of [The New York Times's]\nleft-leaning readers"},{"time":114427,"text":"because of his conservative views,"},{"time":117339,"text":"and more recently, perhaps,\nsome of the right-leaning readers"},{"time":120297,"text":"because of his criticism\nof some aspects of Trump."},{"time":124348,"text":"Yet, his columns are usually"},{"time":126748,"text":"the top one, two or three\nmost-read content of the day"},{"time":131168,"text":"because they're brilliant,"},{"time":132432,"text":"because they bring psychology\nand social science"},{"time":134755,"text":"to providing understanding\nfor what's going on."},{"time":138232,"text":"So without further ado, a huge welcome\nto Gretchen and David."},{"time":141529,"text":"Come and join me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142711,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146448,"text":"So, Gretchen."},{"time":149474,"text":"Sixty-three million Americans\nvoted for Donald Trump."},{"time":154505,"text":"Why did they do this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156243,"text":"Gretchen Carlson: There are a lot\nof reasons, in my mind, why it happened."},{"time":159787,"text":"I mean, I think it was a movement\nof sorts, but it started long ago."},{"time":163086,"text":"It didn't just happen overnight."},{"time":164918,"text":"\"Anger\" would be the first word\nthat I would think of --"},{"time":167853,"text":"anger with nothing\nbeing done in Washington,"},{"time":172140,"text":"anger about not being heard."},{"time":175976,"text":"I think there was a huge swath\nof the population"},{"time":178395,"text":"that feels like Washington\nnever listens to them,"},{"time":181168,"text":"you know, a good part of the middle\nof America, not just the coasts,"},{"time":185426,"text":"and he was somebody they felt\nwas listening to their concerns."},{"time":190156,"text":"So I think those two issues\nwould be the main reason."},{"time":194406,"text":"I have to throw in there also celebrity."},{"time":197392,"text":"I think that had a huge impact\non Donald Trump becoming president."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203082,"text":"CA: Was the anger justified?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":206051,"text":"David Brooks: Yeah, I think so."},{"time":207648,"text":"In 2015 and early 2016,\nI wrote about 30 columns"},{"time":211746,"text":"with the following theme:"},{"time":213121,"text":"don't worry, Donald Trump will never\nbe the Republican nominee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216132,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":217316,"text":"And having done that\nand gotten that so wrong,"},{"time":219538,"text":"I decided to spend the ensuing year\njust out in Trumpworld,"},{"time":222746,"text":"and I found a lot of economic dislocation."},{"time":225640,"text":"I ran into a woman in West Virginia\nwho was going to a funeral for her mom."},{"time":229234,"text":"She said, \"The nice thing about\nbeing Catholic is we don't have to speak,"},{"time":232726,"text":"and that's good,\nbecause we're not word people.\""},{"time":235022,"text":"That phrase rung in my head: word people."},{"time":237028,"text":"A lot of us in the TED community\nare word people,"},{"time":239828,"text":"but if you're not, the economy\nhas not been angled toward you,"},{"time":242979,"text":"and so 11 million men, for example,\nare out of the labor force"},{"time":246640,"text":"because those jobs are done away."},{"time":248273,"text":"A lot of social injury."},{"time":249837,"text":"You used to be able to say,\n\"I'm not the richest person in the world,"},{"time":253158,"text":"I'm not the most famous,"},{"time":254400,"text":"but my neighbors can count on me\nand I get some dignity out of that.\""},{"time":257729,"text":"And because of celebritification\nor whatever, if you're not rich or famous,"},{"time":261307,"text":"you feel invisible."},{"time":262489,"text":"And a lot of moral injury,\nsense of feeling betrayed,"},{"time":265825,"text":"and frankly, in this country,\nwe almost have one success story,"},{"time":269704,"text":"which is you go to college, get\na white-collar job, and you're a success,"},{"time":273298,"text":"and if you don't fit in that formula,"},{"time":275410,"text":"you feel like you're not respected."},{"time":277191,"text":"And so that accumulation of things --"},{"time":279033,"text":"and when I talked to Trump\nvoters and still do,"},{"time":281249,"text":"I found most of them completely\nrealistic about his failings,"},{"time":284958,"text":"but they said, this is my shot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287334,"text":"GC: And yet I predicted\nthat he would be the nominee,"},{"time":290604,"text":"because I've known him for 27 years."},{"time":292812,"text":"He's a master marketer,"},{"time":294626,"text":"and one of the things\nhe did extremely well"},{"time":296653,"text":"that President Obama also did\nextremely well,"},{"time":298871,"text":"was simplifying the message,"},{"time":300933,"text":"simplifying down to phrases"},{"time":303745,"text":"and to a populist message."},{"time":305818,"text":"Even if he can't achieve it,\nit sounded good."},{"time":309575,"text":"And many people latched on\nto that simplicity again."},{"time":312829,"text":"It's something they could grasp onto:"},{"time":314798,"text":"\"I get that. I want that.\nThat sounds fantastic.\""},{"time":318951,"text":"And I remember when he used to come\non my show originally,"},{"time":321899,"text":"before \"The Apprentice\"\nwas even \"The Apprentice,\""},{"time":324324,"text":"and he'd say it was the number\none show on TV."},{"time":326527,"text":"I'd say back to him, \"No, it's not.\""},{"time":328308,"text":"And he would say, \"Yes it is, Gretchen.\""},{"time":330242,"text":"And I would say, \"No it's not.\""},{"time":332150,"text":"But people at home would see that,\nand they'd be like,"},{"time":334709,"text":"\"Wow, I should be watching\nthe number one show on TV.\""},{"time":337309,"text":"And -- lo and behold -- it became\nthe number one show on TV."},{"time":340286,"text":"So he had this, I've seen\nthis ability in him"},{"time":343612,"text":"to be the master marketer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345834,"text":"CA: It's puzzling\nto a lot of people on the left"},{"time":348442,"text":"that so many women voted for him,"},{"time":351725,"text":"despite some of his comments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353286,"text":"GC: I wrote a column\nabout this for Time Motto,"},{"time":356025,"text":"saying that I really believe\nthat lot of people put on blinders,"},{"time":361324,"text":"and maybe for the first time,"},{"time":364207,"text":"some people decided\nthat policies they believed in"},{"time":367003,"text":"and being heard\nand not being invisible anymore"},{"time":369575,"text":"was more important to them"},{"time":371550,"text":"than the way in which he had acted\nor acts as a human."},{"time":375911,"text":"And so human dignity --"},{"time":377983,"text":"whether it would be the dust-up\nabout the disabled reporter,"},{"time":381475,"text":"or what happened\nin that audiotape with Billy Bush"},{"time":384039,"text":"and the way in which he spoke\nabout women --"},{"time":387301,"text":"they put that aside"},{"time":389272,"text":"and pretended as if\nthey hadn't seen that or heard that,"},{"time":391917,"text":"because to them,\npolicies were more important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395977,"text":"CA: Right, so just because\nsomeone voted for Trump,"},{"time":398812,"text":"it's not blind adherence to everything\nthat he's said or stood for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402563,"text":"GC: No. I heard a lot of people\nthat would say to me,"},{"time":405409,"text":"\"Wow, I just wish he would shut up\nbefore the election."},{"time":408496,"text":"If he would just stay quiet,\nhe'd get elected.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":412083,"text":"CA: And so, maybe for people on the left\nthere's a trap there,"},{"time":415044,"text":"to sort of despise\nor just be baffled by the support,"},{"time":420646,"text":"assuming that it's for some\nof the unattractive features."},{"time":423754,"text":"Actually, maybe they're supporting\nhim despite those,"},{"time":426323,"text":"because they see something exciting."},{"time":428133,"text":"They see a man of action."},{"time":429499,"text":"They see the choking hold of government\nbeing thrown off in some way"},{"time":434581,"text":"and they're excited by that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435944,"text":"GC: But don't forget we saw that\non the left as well -- Bernie Sanders."},{"time":439344,"text":"So this is one of the commonalities\nthat I think we can talk about today,"},{"time":443322,"text":"\"The Year of the Outsider,\"\nDavid -- right?"},{"time":447003,"text":"And even though Bernie Sanders\nhas been in Congress for a long time,"},{"time":450292,"text":"he was deemed an outsider this time."},{"time":452529,"text":"And so there was anger\non the left as well,"},{"time":454895,"text":"and so many people were in favor\nof Bernie Sanders."},{"time":458854,"text":"So I see it as a commonality."},{"time":462766,"text":"People who like Trump,\npeople who like Bernie Sanders,"},{"time":465369,"text":"they were liking different policies,\nbut the underpinning was anger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469196,"text":"CA: David, there's often\nthis narrative, then,"},{"time":473790,"text":"that the sole explanation\nfor Trump's victory and his rise"},{"time":479005,"text":"is his tapping into anger\nin a very visceral way."},{"time":483981,"text":"But you've written a bit about\nthat it's actually more than that,"},{"time":488663,"text":"that there's a worldview\nthat's being worked on here."},{"time":491885,"text":"Could you talk about that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":493182,"text":"DB: I would say he understood what,\nfrankly, I didn't,"},{"time":495761,"text":"which is what debate we were having."},{"time":497641,"text":"And so I'd grown up starting with Reagan,"},{"time":500098,"text":"and it was the big government\nversus small government debate."},{"time":503026,"text":"It was Barry Goldwater\nversus George McGovern,"},{"time":505239,"text":"and that was the debate\nwe had been having for a generation."},{"time":509368,"text":"It was: Democrats wanted to use\ngovernment to enhance equality,"},{"time":513557,"text":"Republicans wanted to limit government\nto enhance freedom."},{"time":516329,"text":"That was the debate."},{"time":517536,"text":"He understood what I think\nthe two major parties did not,"},{"time":520370,"text":"which was that's not the debate anymore."},{"time":522338,"text":"The debate is now open versus closed."},{"time":524691,"text":"On one side are those who have\nthe tailwinds of globalization"},{"time":527981,"text":"and the meritocracy blowing at their back,"},{"time":530238,"text":"and they tend to favor open trade,"},{"time":532661,"text":"open borders, open social mores,"},{"time":534670,"text":"because there are so many opportunities."},{"time":536656,"text":"On the other side are those\nwho feel the headwinds of globalization"},{"time":540136,"text":"and the meritocracy\njust blasting in their faces,"},{"time":542552,"text":"and they favor closed trade,\nclosed borders, closed social mores,"},{"time":546507,"text":"because they just want some security."},{"time":548622,"text":"And so he was right\non that fundamental issue,"},{"time":550790,"text":"and people were willing\nto overlook a lot to get there."},{"time":553466,"text":"And so he felt that sense of security."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555597,"text":"We're speaking the morning after\nTrump's joint session speech."},{"time":559950,"text":"There are three traditional\ngroups in the Republican Party."},{"time":562800,"text":"There are the foreign policies hawks"},{"time":564602,"text":"who believe in America\nas global policeman."},{"time":566681,"text":"Trump totally repudiated that view."},{"time":568558,"text":"Second, there was the social conservatives"},{"time":570628,"text":"who believed in religious liberty,"},{"time":572359,"text":"pro-life,"},{"time":574296,"text":"prayer in schools."},{"time":577710,"text":"He totally ignored that."},{"time":579379,"text":"There was not a single mention\nof a single social conservative issue."},{"time":582838,"text":"And then there were the fiscal hawks,"},{"time":584681,"text":"the people who wanted to cut down\non the national debt, Tea Party,"},{"time":587823,"text":"cut the size of government."},{"time":589153,"text":"He's expanding the size of government!"},{"time":591032,"text":"Here's a man who has single-handedly\nrevolutionized a major American party"},{"time":594738,"text":"because he understood\nwhere the debate was headed"},{"time":597735,"text":"before other people."},{"time":599106,"text":"And then guys like Steve Bannon come in"},{"time":601145,"text":"and give him substance to his impulses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604207,"text":"CA: And so take that a bit further,"},{"time":606000,"text":"and maybe expand a bit more\non your insights"},{"time":609779,"text":"into Steve Bannon's worldview."},{"time":612066,"text":"Because he's sometimes tarred\nin very simple terms"},{"time":614822,"text":"as this dangerous, racist,\nxenophobic, anger-sparking person."},{"time":621457,"text":"There's more to the story;\nthat is perhaps an unfair simplification."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625997,"text":"DB: I think that part is true,"},{"time":627457,"text":"but there's another part\nthat's probably true, too."},{"time":629951,"text":"He's part of a global movement."},{"time":632135,"text":"It's like being around Marxists in 1917."},{"time":634844,"text":"There's him here, there's the UKIP party,\nthere's the National Front in France,"},{"time":639064,"text":"there's Putin, there's a Turkish version,\na Philippine version."},{"time":642133,"text":"So we have to recognize that this\nis a global intellectual movement."},{"time":645628,"text":"And it believes"},{"time":646867,"text":"that wisdom and virtue is not held\nin individual conversation and civility"},{"time":652148,"text":"the way a lot of us\nin the enlightenment side of the world do."},{"time":655574,"text":"It's held in -- the German word\nis the \"volk\" -- in the people,"},{"time":659176,"text":"in the common, instinctive wisdom\nof the plain people."},{"time":662730,"text":"And the essential virtue of that people\nis always being threatened by outsiders."},{"time":667702,"text":"And he's got a strategy\nfor how to get there."},{"time":670409,"text":"He's got a series of policies\nto bring the people up"},{"time":674461,"text":"and repudiate the outsiders,"},{"time":676811,"text":"whether those outsiders\nare Islam, Mexicans, the media,"},{"time":681604,"text":"the coastal elites..."},{"time":683498,"text":"And there's a whole worldview there;\nit's a very coherent worldview."},{"time":686835,"text":"I sort of have more respect for him."},{"time":688758,"text":"I loathe what he stands for\nand I think he's wrong on the substance,"},{"time":692033,"text":"but it's interesting to see someone\nwith a set of ideas"},{"time":694764,"text":"find a vehicle, Donald Trump,"},{"time":696761,"text":"and then try to take control\nof the White House"},{"time":699903,"text":"in order to advance his viewpoint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702029,"text":"CA: So it's almost become, like,\nthat the core question of our time now is:"},{"time":706879,"text":"Can you be patriotic\nbut also have a global mindset?"},{"time":711924,"text":"Are these two things\nimplacably opposed to each other?"},{"time":716219,"text":"I mean, a lot of conservatives"},{"time":719704,"text":"and, to the extent\nthat it's a different category,"},{"time":722175,"text":"a lot of Trump supporters,"},{"time":723480,"text":"are infuriated by the coastal elites\nand the globalists"},{"time":727430,"text":"because they see them\nas, sort of, not cheering for America,"},{"time":731440,"text":"not embracing fully American values."},{"time":734126,"text":"I mean, have you seen that\nin your conversations with people,"},{"time":737702,"text":"in your understanding of their mindset?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":739630,"text":"GC: I do think that there's\na huge difference between --"},{"time":742855,"text":"I hate to put people in categories, but,"},{"time":744861,"text":"Middle America versus\npeople who live on the coasts."},{"time":748846,"text":"It's an entirely different existence."},{"time":750936,"text":"And I grew up in Minnesota, so I have\nan understanding of Middle America,"},{"time":754626,"text":"and I've never forgotten it."},{"time":756006,"text":"And maybe that's why I have\nan understanding of what happened here,"},{"time":759537,"text":"because those people often feel\nlike nobody's listening to them,"},{"time":764385,"text":"and that we're only concentrating\non California and New York."},{"time":768897,"text":"And so I think that was a huge reason\nwhy Trump was elected."},{"time":773445,"text":"I mean, these people felt like\nthey were being heard."},{"time":777557,"text":"Whether or not patriotism falls into that,"},{"time":781731,"text":"I'm not sure about that."},{"time":782924,"text":"I do know one thing:"},{"time":784119,"text":"a lot of things Trump talked about\nlast night are not conservative things."},{"time":788198,"text":"Had Hillary Clinton gotten up\nand given that speech,"},{"time":790699,"text":"not one Republican would have\nstood up to applaud."},{"time":793080,"text":"I mean, he's talking about spending\na trillion dollars on infrastructure."},{"time":796731,"text":"That is not a conservative viewpoint."},{"time":798593,"text":"He talked about government-mandated\nmaternity leave."},{"time":802312,"text":"A lot of women may love that;\nit's not a conservative viewpoint."},{"time":805354,"text":"So it's fascinating"},{"time":806529,"text":"that people who loved what his message\nwas during the campaign,"},{"time":810253,"text":"I'm not sure -- how do you\nthink they'll react to that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":812879,"text":"DB: I should say I grew up\nin Lower Manhattan,"},{"time":815089,"text":"in the triangle between ABC Carpets,\nthe Strand Bookstore"},{"time":817844,"text":"and The Odeon restaurant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819182,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":820837,"text":"GC: Come to Minnesota sometime!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":822715,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":823972,"text":"CA: You are a card-carrying member\nof the coastal elite, my man."},{"time":829646,"text":"But what did you make\nof the speech last night?"},{"time":831922,"text":"It seemed to be a move\nto a more moderate position,"},{"time":835393,"text":"on the face of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836568,"text":"DB: Yeah, I thought it\nwas his best speech,"},{"time":838619,"text":"and it took away the freakishness of him."},{"time":840681,"text":"I do think he's a moral freak,"},{"time":842561,"text":"and I think he'll be undone by that fact,"},{"time":845387,"text":"the fact that he just doesn't know\nanything about anything"},{"time":848190,"text":"and is uncurious about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849467,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":850584,"text":"But if you take away these minor flaws,"},{"time":852773,"text":"I think we got to see him at his best,"},{"time":854869,"text":"and it was revealing for me\nto see him at his best,"},{"time":858011,"text":"because to me, it exposed a central\ncontradiction that he's got to confront,"},{"time":862552,"text":"that a lot of what he's doing\nis offering security."},{"time":865580,"text":"So, \"I'm ordering closed borders,"},{"time":867402,"text":"I'm going to secure the world\nfor you, for my people.\""},{"time":870289,"text":"But then if you actually look\nat a lot of his economic policies,"},{"time":873361,"text":"like health care reform, which is about\nprivate health care accounts,"},{"time":877166,"text":"that's not security, that's risk."},{"time":880055,"text":"Educational vouchers: that's risk.\nDeregulation: that's risk."},{"time":883775,"text":"There's really a contradiction\nbetween the security of the mindset"},{"time":887776,"text":"and a lot of the policies,\nwhich are very risk-oriented."},{"time":890584,"text":"And what I would say, especially\nhaving spent this year,"},{"time":894109,"text":"the people in rural Minnesota,\nin New Mexico --"},{"time":897998,"text":"they've got enough risk in their lives."},{"time":900087,"text":"And so they're going to say,\n\"No thank you.\""},{"time":903426,"text":"And I think his health care repeal\nwill fail for that reason."}]},{"cues":[{"time":907218,"text":"CA: But despite the criticisms\nyou just made of him,"},{"time":910187,"text":"it does at least seem that he's listening"},{"time":914423,"text":"to a surprisingly wide range of voices;"},{"time":916621,"text":"it's not like everyone\nis coming from the same place."},{"time":919416,"text":"And maybe that leads to a certain\namount of chaos and confusion, but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":924700,"text":"GC: I actually don't think he's listening\nto a wide range of voices."},{"time":927946,"text":"I think he's listening to very few people."},{"time":930000,"text":"That's just my impression of it."},{"time":931827,"text":"I believe that some of the things\nhe said last night"},{"time":934306,"text":"had Ivanka all over them."},{"time":936353,"text":"So I believe he was listening\nto her before that speech."},{"time":940291,"text":"And he was Teleprompter Trump\nlast night, as opposed to Twitter Trump."},{"time":944538,"text":"And that's why, before we came out here,"},{"time":946687,"text":"I said, \"We better check Twitter\nto see if anything's changed.\""},{"time":950922,"text":"And also I think you have to keep in mind"},{"time":953135,"text":"that because he's such a unique character,"},{"time":956342,"text":"what was the bar that we\nwere expecting last night?"},{"time":959211,"text":"Was it here or here or here?"},{"time":962091,"text":"And so he comes out\nand gives a looking political speech,"},{"time":965877,"text":"and everyone goes, \"Wow! He can do it.\""},{"time":969289,"text":"It just depends\non which direction he goes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971335,"text":"DB: Yeah, and we're trying\nto build bridges here,"},{"time":973724,"text":"and especially for an audience\nthat may have contempt for Trump,"},{"time":976785,"text":"it's important to say,\nno, this is a real thing."},{"time":979058,"text":"But as I try my best to go an hour\nshowing respect for him,"},{"time":982936,"text":"my thyroid is surging,"},{"time":984951,"text":"because I think the oddities\nof his character"},{"time":988347,"text":"really are condemnatory\nand are going to doom him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":990852,"text":"CA: Your reputation is as a conservative."},{"time":996334,"text":"People would you describe you\nas right of center,"},{"time":998732,"text":"and yet here you are\nwith this visceral reaction against him"},{"time":1002989,"text":"and some of what he stands for."},{"time":1004639,"text":"I mean, I'm -- how do you have\na conversation?"},{"time":1008290,"text":"The people who support him,\non evidence so far,"},{"time":1011243,"text":"are probably pretty excited."},{"time":1013459,"text":"He's certainly shown real engagement"},{"time":1018641,"text":"in a lot of what he promised to do,"},{"time":1020781,"text":"and there is a strong desire\nto change the system radically."},{"time":1024906,"text":"People hate what government has become\nand how it's left them out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029060,"text":"GC: I totally agree with that,"},{"time":1030866,"text":"but I think that when he was proposing\na huge government program last night"},{"time":1034557,"text":"that we used to call the bad s-word,\n\"stimulus,\" I find it completely ironic."},{"time":1038649,"text":"To spend a trillion dollars\non something --"},{"time":1040681,"text":"that is not a conservative viewpoint."},{"time":1042480,"text":"Then again, I don't really believe\nhe's a Republican."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044990,"text":"DB: And I would say, as someone\nwho identifies as conservative:"},{"time":1048035,"text":"first of all,"},{"time":1049222,"text":"to be conservative is to believe\nin the limitations of politics."},{"time":1052284,"text":"Samuel Johnson said, \"Of all the things\nthat human hearts endure,"},{"time":1055426,"text":"how few are those that kings\ncan cause and cure.\""},{"time":1057897,"text":"Politics is a limited realm;"},{"time":1059566,"text":"what matters most\nis the moral nature of the society."},{"time":1062627,"text":"And so I have to think\ncharacter comes first,"},{"time":1064820,"text":"and a man who doesn't pass\nthe character threshold"},{"time":1067217,"text":"cannot be a good president."},{"time":1068581,"text":"Second, I'm the kind\nof conservative who --"},{"time":1071270,"text":"I harken back to Alexander Hamilton,"},{"time":1073981,"text":"who was a Latino hip-hop star\nfrom the heights --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076335,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1080434,"text":"but his definition of America\nwas very future-oriented."},{"time":1085829,"text":"He was a poor boy from the islands"},{"time":1088209,"text":"who had this rapid and amazing\nrise to success,"},{"time":1092546,"text":"and he wanted government to give\npoor boys and girls like him"},{"time":1095523,"text":"a chance to succeed,"},{"time":1096701,"text":"using limited but energetic government\nto create social mobility."},{"time":1099946,"text":"For him and for Lincoln\nand for Teddy Roosevelt,"},{"time":1103554,"text":"the idea of America\nwas the idea of the future."},{"time":1105913,"text":"We may have division and racism\nand slavery in our past,"},{"time":1108828,"text":"but we have a common future."},{"time":1110744,"text":"The definition of America that Steve\nBannon stands for is backwards-looking."},{"time":1114966,"text":"It's nostalgic; it's for the past."},{"time":1116937,"text":"And that is not traditionally\nthe American identity."},{"time":1119441,"text":"That's traditionally, frankly,\nthe Russian identity."},{"time":1121925,"text":"That's how they define virtue."},{"time":1123431,"text":"And so I think it is a fundamental\nand foundational betrayal"},{"time":1126308,"text":"of what conservatism used to stand for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1128261,"text":"CA: Well, I'd like actually\nlike to hear from you,"},{"time":1130633,"text":"and if we see some comments coming in\nfrom some of you, we'll --"},{"time":1133679,"text":"oh, well here's one right now."},{"time":1135175,"text":"Jeffrey Alan Carnegie: I've tried\nto convince progressive friends"},{"time":1138339,"text":"that they need to understand\nwhat motivates Trump supporters,"},{"time":1141255,"text":"yet many of them have given up\ntrying to understand"},{"time":1143696,"text":"in the face of what they perceive\nas lies, selfishness and hatred."},{"time":1146864,"text":"How would you reach out to such people,\nthe Tea Party of the left,"},{"time":1150073,"text":"to try to bridge this divide?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1153078,"text":"GC: I actually think\nthere are commonalities in anger,"},{"time":1156180,"text":"as I expressed earlier."},{"time":1157642,"text":"So I think you can come to the table,\nboth being passionate about something."},{"time":1162096,"text":"So at least you care."},{"time":1164435,"text":"And I would like to believe --\nthe c-word has also become"},{"time":1168166,"text":"a horrible word -- \"compromise,\" right?"},{"time":1170766,"text":"So you have the far left\nand the far right,"},{"time":1172861,"text":"and compromise -- forget it."},{"time":1174268,"text":"Those groups don't want\nto even think about it."},{"time":1176573,"text":"But you have a huge swath\nof voters, myself included,"},{"time":1179687,"text":"who are registered independents,"},{"time":1181439,"text":"like 40 percent of us, right?"},{"time":1183431,"text":"So there is a huge faction of America\nthat wants to see change"},{"time":1187756,"text":"and wants to see people come together."},{"time":1190414,"text":"It's just that we have to figure out"},{"time":1192204,"text":"how to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1193639,"text":"CA: So let's talk about that for a minute,"},{"time":1195781,"text":"because we're having these TED Dialogues,\nwe're trying to bridge."},{"time":1199025,"text":"There's a lot of people out there,\nright now, perhaps especially on the left,"},{"time":1202725,"text":"who think this is a terrible idea,"},{"time":1204540,"text":"that actually, the only moral response\nto the great tyranny"},{"time":1210503,"text":"that may be about to emerge in America"},{"time":1214538,"text":"is to resist it at every stage,\nis to fight it tooth and nail,"},{"time":1218194,"text":"it's a mistake to try and do this."},{"time":1220099,"text":"Just fight!"},{"time":1222001,"text":"Is there a case for that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1224370,"text":"DB: It depends what \"fight\" means.\nIf it means literal fighting, then no."},{"time":1227974,"text":"If it means marching, well maybe\nmarching to raise consciousness,"},{"time":1231122,"text":"that seems fine."},{"time":1232411,"text":"But if you want change in this country,\nwe do it through parties and politics."},{"time":1236566,"text":"We organize parties, and those parties\nare big, diverse, messy coalitions,"},{"time":1241367,"text":"and we engage in politics,"},{"time":1243009,"text":"and politics is always\nmorally unsatisfying"},{"time":1245361,"text":"because it's always\na bunch of compromises."},{"time":1247862,"text":"But politics is essentially\na competition between partial truths."},{"time":1251668,"text":"The Trump people have a piece\nof the truth in America."},{"time":1254327,"text":"I think Trump himself is the wrong answer\nto the right question,"},{"time":1257464,"text":"but they have some truth,"},{"time":1259499,"text":"and it's truth found in the epidemic\nof opiates around the country,"},{"time":1263672,"text":"it's truth found in\nthe spread of loneliness,"},{"time":1266688,"text":"it's the truth found in people\nwhose lives are inverted."},{"time":1269671,"text":"They peaked professionally at age 30,"},{"time":1272117,"text":"and it's all been downhill since."},{"time":1274166,"text":"And so, understanding that\ndoesn't take fighting,"},{"time":1276704,"text":"it takes conversation and then asking,"},{"time":1278679,"text":"\"What are we going to replace Trump with?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1280713,"text":"GC: But you saw fighting last night,\neven at the speech,"},{"time":1283404,"text":"because you saw the Democratic women\nwho came and wore white"},{"time":1286296,"text":"to honor the suffragette movement."},{"time":1288028,"text":"I remember back during the campaign"},{"time":1290079,"text":"where some Trump supporters wanted\nto actually get rid of the amendment"},{"time":1293592,"text":"that allowed us to vote as women."},{"time":1295330,"text":"It was like, what?"},{"time":1297522,"text":"So I don't know if\nthat's the right way to fight."},{"time":1299872,"text":"It was interesting,\nbecause I was looking in the audience,"},{"time":1302704,"text":"trying to see Democratic women\nwho didn't wear white."},{"time":1305283,"text":"So there's a lot going on there,"},{"time":1306857,"text":"and there's a lot of ways to fight\nthat are not necessarily doing that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1313516,"text":"CA: I mean, one of the key\nquestions, to me, is:"},{"time":1316014,"text":"The people who voted for Trump\nbut, if you like, are more in the center,"},{"time":1321687,"text":"like they're possibly\namenable to persuasion --"},{"time":1325293,"text":"are they more likely to be persuaded\nby seeing a passionate uprising"},{"time":1331108,"text":"of people saying, \"No, no, no, you can't!\""},{"time":1334645,"text":"or will that actually piss them off\nand push them away?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1338583,"text":"DB: How are any of us persuaded?"},{"time":1340255,"text":"Am I going to persuade you by saying,\n\"Well, you're kind of a bigot,"},{"time":1343606,"text":"you're supporting bigotry,\nyou're supporting sexism."},{"time":1346571,"text":"You're a primitive, fascistic rise\nfrom some authoritarian past\"?"},{"time":1351223,"text":"That's probably not going to be\ntoo persuasive to you."},{"time":1353932,"text":"And so the way any of us\nare persuaded is by:"},{"time":1356597,"text":"a) some basic show of respect\nfor the point of view, and saying,"},{"time":1360963,"text":"\"I think this guy is not going\nto get you where you need to go.\""},{"time":1364306,"text":"And there are two phrases\nyou've heard over and over again,"},{"time":1367710,"text":"wherever you go in the country."},{"time":1369227,"text":"One, the phrase \"flyover country.\""},{"time":1371142,"text":"And that's been heard for years,"},{"time":1373014,"text":"but I would say this year,\nI heard it almost on an hourly basis,"},{"time":1376734,"text":"a sense of feeling invisible."},{"time":1378269,"text":"And then the sense a sense of the phrase\n\"political correctness.\""},{"time":1382051,"text":"Just that rebellion: \"They're not even\nletting us say what we think.\""},{"time":1386154,"text":"And I teach at Yale."},{"time":1387503,"text":"The narrowing of debate is real."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1392449,"text":"CA: So you would say this is a trap\nthat liberals have fallen into"},{"time":1395677,"text":"by celebrating causes\nthey really believe in,"},{"time":1398797,"text":"often expressed through the language\nof \"political correctness.\""},{"time":1402783,"text":"They have done damage.\nThey have pushed people away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1407142,"text":"DB: I would say\na lot of the argument, though,"},{"time":1409314,"text":"with \"descent to fascism,\"\n\"authoritarianism\" --"},{"time":1411699,"text":"that just feels over-the-top to people."},{"time":1413912,"text":"And listen, I've written\neight million anti-Trump columns,"},{"time":1416719,"text":"but it is a problem, especially\nfor the coastal media,"},{"time":1419413,"text":"that every time he does something\nslightly wrong, we go to 11,"},{"time":1423610,"text":"and we're at 11 every day."},{"time":1425820,"text":"And it just strains\ncredibility at some point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1428684,"text":"CA: Crying wolf a little too loud\nand a little too early."},{"time":1431434,"text":"But there may be a time\nwhen we really do have to cry wolf."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1434325,"text":"GC: But see -- one of the most\nimportant things to me"},{"time":1436921,"text":"is how the conservative media\nhandles Trump."},{"time":1440439,"text":"Will they call him out\nwhen things are not true,"},{"time":1445036,"text":"or will they just go along with it?"},{"time":1447243,"text":"To me, that is what is essential\nin this entire discussion,"},{"time":1451296,"text":"because when you have\nfollowers of somebody"},{"time":1455904,"text":"who don't really care\nif he tells the truth or not,"},{"time":1459560,"text":"that can be very dangerous."},{"time":1461869,"text":"So to me, it's: How is the conservative\nmedia going to respond to it?"},{"time":1466179,"text":"I mean, you've been calling them out."},{"time":1468697,"text":"But how will other forms\nof conservative media deal with that"},{"time":1473106,"text":"as we move forward?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1474288,"text":"DB: It's all shifted, though."},{"time":1475708,"text":"The conservative media used to be Fox\nor Charles Krauthammer or George Will."},{"time":1479370,"text":"They're no longer the conservative media."},{"time":1481398,"text":"Now there's another whole set\nof institutions further right,"},{"time":1484253,"text":"which is Breitbart and Infowars,\nAlex Jones, Laura Ingraham,"},{"time":1489874,"text":"and so they're the ones who are now\nhis base, not even so much Fox."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1493699,"text":"CA: My last question for the time being\nis just on this question of the truth."},{"time":1497810,"text":"I mean, it's one of the scariest\nthings to people right now,"},{"time":1500713,"text":"that there is no agreement,\nnationally, on what is true."},{"time":1504420,"text":"I've never seen anything like it,"},{"time":1506234,"text":"where facts are so massively disputed."},{"time":1509595,"text":"Your whole newspaper, sir,\nis delivering fake news every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1513170,"text":"DB: And failing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1514702,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1515814,"text":"CA: And failing. My commiserations."},{"time":1517794,"text":"But is there any path"},{"time":1524108,"text":"whereby we can start to get\nsome kind of consensus,"},{"time":1527942,"text":"to believe the same things?"},{"time":1530826,"text":"Can online communities play a role here?"},{"time":1534418,"text":"How do we fix this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1535611,"text":"GC: See, I understand how that happened."},{"time":1537673,"text":"That's another groundswell kind of emotion"},{"time":1539896,"text":"that was going on in the middle of America"},{"time":1541935,"text":"and not being heard,"},{"time":1543192,"text":"in thinking that the mainstream\nmedia was biased."},{"time":1546247,"text":"There's a difference, though,\nbetween being biased and being fake."},{"time":1550337,"text":"To me, that is a very important\ndistinction in this conversation."},{"time":1553934,"text":"So let's just say that there was some bias\nin the mainstream media."},{"time":1558456,"text":"OK. So there are ways\nto try and mend that."},{"time":1561413,"text":"But what Trump's doing\nis nuclearizing that and saying,"},{"time":1565512,"text":"\"Look, we're just going to call\nall of that fake.\""},{"time":1568074,"text":"That's where it gets dangerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1569644,"text":"CA: Do you think enough of his supporters"},{"time":1572529,"text":"have a greater loyalty\nto the truth than to any ..."},{"time":1576798,"text":"Like, the principle\nof not supporting something"},{"time":1581461,"text":"that is demonstrably not true"},{"time":1583483,"text":"actually matters, so there will be\na correction at some point?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1586468,"text":"DB: I think the truth\neventually comes out."},{"time":1588782,"text":"So for example, Donald Trump\nhas based a lot of his economic policy"},{"time":1591962,"text":"on this supposition that Americans\nhave lost manufacturing jobs"},{"time":1594990,"text":"because they've been stolen\nby the Chinese."},{"time":1597056,"text":"That is maybe 13 percent\nof the jobs that left."},{"time":1600006,"text":"The truth is that 87 percent of the jobs\nwere replaced by technology."},{"time":1603612,"text":"That is just the truth."},{"time":1605414,"text":"And so as a result, when he says,"},{"time":1608100,"text":"\"I'm going to close TPP\nand all the jobs will come roaring back,\""},{"time":1612091,"text":"they will not come roaring back."},{"time":1613676,"text":"So that is an actual fact, in my belief."},{"time":1616784,"text":"And --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1617966,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1619289,"text":"GC: But I'm saying what\nhis supporters think is the truth,"},{"time":1622029,"text":"no matter how many times\nyou might say that,"},{"time":1624188,"text":"they still believe him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1625418,"text":"DB: But eventually either jobs\nwill come back or they will not come back,"},{"time":1629201,"text":"and at that point, either something\nwill work or it doesn't work,"},{"time":1632320,"text":"and it doesn't work or not work\nbecause of great marketing,"},{"time":1635139,"text":"it works because it actually\naddresses a real problem"},{"time":1637708,"text":"and so I happen to think\nthe truth will out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1640218,"text":"CA: If you've got a question,\nplease raise your hand here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1644185,"text":"Yael Eisenstat: I'll speak into the box."},{"time":1646829,"text":"My name's Yael Eisenstat."},{"time":1649847,"text":"I hear a lot of this talk"},{"time":1651482,"text":"about how we all need to start\ntalking to each other more"},{"time":1654185,"text":"and understanding each other more,"},{"time":1655885,"text":"and I've even written about this,\npublished on this subject as well,"},{"time":1659449,"text":"but now today I keep hearing liberals --\nyes, I live in New York,"},{"time":1664583,"text":"I can be considered a liberal --"},{"time":1666330,"text":"we sit here and self-analyze:"},{"time":1668053,"text":"What did we do to not understand\nthe Rust Belt?"},{"time":1670386,"text":"Or: What can we do to understand\nMiddle America better?"},{"time":1673260,"text":"And what I'd like to know:"},{"time":1674732,"text":"Have you seen any attempts\nor conversations from Middle America"},{"time":1678682,"text":"of what can I do to understand\nthe so-called coastal elites better?"},{"time":1681923,"text":"Because I'm just offended\nas being put in a box as a coastal elite"},{"time":1685950,"text":"as someone in Middle America is\nas being considered a flyover state"},{"time":1689198,"text":"and not listened to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1690699,"text":"CA: There you go, I can hear Facebook\ncheering as you --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1693466,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1694590,"text":"DB: I would say -- and this is someone\nwho has been conservative"},{"time":1698164,"text":"all my adult life --"},{"time":1699354,"text":"when you grow up conservative,"},{"time":1701145,"text":"you learn to speak both languages."},{"time":1703806,"text":"Because if I'm going to listen to music,"},{"time":1706234,"text":"I'm not going to listen to Ted Nugent."},{"time":1708376,"text":"So a lot of my favorite rock bands\nare all on the left."},{"time":1713081,"text":"If I'm going to go to a school,"},{"time":1714643,"text":"I'm going probably to school\nwhere the culture is liberal."},{"time":1717420,"text":"If I'm going to watch a sitcom"},{"time":1719051,"text":"or a late-night comedy show,\nit's going to be liberal."},{"time":1721638,"text":"If I'm going to read a good newspaper,\nit'll be the New York Times."},{"time":1724845,"text":"As a result, you learn\nto speak both languages."},{"time":1727135,"text":"And that actually, at least\nfor a number of years,"},{"time":1730043,"text":"when I started at National Review\nwith William F. Buckley,"},{"time":1732885,"text":"it made us sharper,"},{"time":1734389,"text":"because we were used to arguing\nagainst people every day."},{"time":1738040,"text":"The problem now that's happened\nis you have ghettoization on the right"},{"time":1741373,"text":"and you can live entirely in rightworld,"},{"time":1743758,"text":"so as a result, the quality of argument\non the right has diminished,"},{"time":1747253,"text":"because you're not in the other side"},{"time":1749820,"text":"all the time."},{"time":1751097,"text":"But I do think if you're living\nin Minnesota or Iowa or Arizona,"},{"time":1756073,"text":"the coastal elites\nmake themselves aware to you,"},{"time":1758432,"text":"so you know that language as well,"},{"time":1760142,"text":"but it's not the reverse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1761594,"text":"CA: But what does Middle America\nnot get about coastal elites?"},{"time":1765849,"text":"So the critique is,"},{"time":1768913,"text":"you are not dealing\nwith the real problems."},{"time":1771699,"text":"There's a feeling of a snobbishness,\nan elitism that is very off-putting."},{"time":1778184,"text":"What are they missing?"},{"time":1779376,"text":"If you could plant one piece of truth"},{"time":1782903,"text":"from the mindset of someone\nin this room, for example,"},{"time":1788117,"text":"what would you say to them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1790869,"text":"DB: Just how insanely wonderful we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1792808,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1794435,"text":"No, I reject the category."},{"time":1796809,"text":"The problem with populism\nis the same problem with elitism."},{"time":1800317,"text":"It's just a prejudice on the basis"},{"time":1802639,"text":"of probably an over-generalized \nsocial class distinction"},{"time":1805613,"text":"which is too simplistic\nto apply in reality."},{"time":1808692,"text":"Those of us in New York know\nthere are some people in New York"},{"time":1811658,"text":"who are completely awesome,\nand some people who are pathetic,"},{"time":1814609,"text":"and if you live in Iowa, some people\nare awesome and some people are pathetic."},{"time":1818367,"text":"It's not a question\nof what degree you have"},{"time":1820459,"text":"or where you happen to live\nin the country."},{"time":1822531,"text":"The distinction is just a crude\nsimplification to arouse political power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1826029,"text":"GC: But I would encourage people\nto watch a television news show"},{"time":1830638,"text":"or read a column\nthat they normally wouldn't."},{"time":1834221,"text":"So if you are a Trump supporter,\nwatch the other side for a day,"},{"time":1839271,"text":"because you need to come out of the bubble"},{"time":1841316,"text":"if you're ever going\nto have a conversation."},{"time":1843442,"text":"And both sides -- so if you're a liberal,"},{"time":1846080,"text":"then watch something\nthat's very conservative."},{"time":1848935,"text":"Read a column that is not something\nyou would normally read,"},{"time":1852607,"text":"because then you gain perspective\nof what the other side is thinking,"},{"time":1855921,"text":"and to me, that's a start\nof coming together."},{"time":1858405,"text":"I worry about the same thing\nyou worry about, these bubbles."},{"time":1861270,"text":"I think if you only watch\ncertain entities,"},{"time":1863314,"text":"you have no idea what the rest\nof the world is talking about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1866269,"text":"DB: I think not only watching,"},{"time":1868802,"text":"being part of an organization\nthat meets at least once a month"},{"time":1871840,"text":"that puts you in direct contact\nwith people completely unlike yourself"},{"time":1875194,"text":"is something we all have\na responsibility for."},{"time":1877369,"text":"I may get this a little wrong,"},{"time":1878860,"text":"but I think of the top-selling\nautomotive models in this country,"},{"time":1882129,"text":"I think the top three or four\nare all pickup trucks."},{"time":1885475,"text":"So ask yourself: How many people\ndo I know who own a pickup truck?"},{"time":1889311,"text":"And it could be very few or zero\nfor a lot of people."},{"time":1892764,"text":"And that's sort of a warning sign\nkind of a problem."},{"time":1895742,"text":"Where can I join a club"},{"time":1897515,"text":"where I'll have a lot in common\nwith a person who drives a pickup truck"},{"time":1900953,"text":"because we have a common\ninterest in whatever?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1903152,"text":"CA: And so the internet is definitely\ncontributing to this."},{"time":1905988,"text":"A question here from Chris Ajemian:"},{"time":1908165,"text":"\"How do you feel structure\nof communications,"},{"time":1910314,"text":"especially the prevalence of social\nmedia and individualized content,"},{"time":1914068,"text":"can be used to bring together\na political divide,"},{"time":1916562,"text":"instead of just filing communities\ninto echo chambers?\""},{"time":1919821,"text":"I mean, it looks like Facebook\nand Google, since the election,"},{"time":1924294,"text":"are working hard on this question."},{"time":1925997,"text":"They're trying to change the algorithms"},{"time":1929839,"text":"so that they don't amplify fake news"},{"time":1933502,"text":"to the extent that it happened\nlast time round."},{"time":1935932,"text":"Do you see any other\npromising signs of ...?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1938180,"text":"GC: ... or amplify one side\nof the equation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1940307,"text":"CA: Exactly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1941482,"text":"GC: I think that was the constant\nargument from the right,"},{"time":1945871,"text":"that social media\nand the internet in general"},{"time":1948465,"text":"was putting articles towards the top\nthat were not their worldview."},{"time":1952311,"text":"I think, again, that fed into the anger."},{"time":1955277,"text":"It fed into the anger of:"},{"time":1956836,"text":"\"You're pushing something\nthat's not what I believe.\""},{"time":1959640,"text":"But social media has obviously\nchanged everything,"},{"time":1962084,"text":"and I think Trump is the example\nof Twitter changing absolutely everything."},{"time":1966485,"text":"And from his point of view,"},{"time":1968512,"text":"he's reaching the American people\nwithout a filter,"},{"time":1972833,"text":"which he believes the media is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1977365,"text":"CA: Question from the audience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1980498,"text":"Destiny: Hi. I'm Destiny."},{"time":1982347,"text":"I have a question regarding political\ncorrectness, and I'm curious:"},{"time":1986701,"text":"When did political correctness\nbecome synonymous with silencing,"},{"time":1991395,"text":"versus a way that we speak\nabout other people"},{"time":1996534,"text":"to show them respect\nand preserve their dignity?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1999697,"text":"GC: Well, I think the conservative media\nreally pounded this issue"},{"time":2003109,"text":"for the last 10 years."},{"time":2004997,"text":"I think that they really, really\nspent a lot of time"},{"time":2008382,"text":"talking about political correctness,"},{"time":2010212,"text":"and how people should have\nthe ability to say what they think."},{"time":2013639,"text":"Another reason why Trump\nbecame so popular:"},{"time":2015833,"text":"because he says what he thinks."},{"time":2017735,"text":"It also makes me think about the fact"},{"time":2023756,"text":"that I do believe there are a lot\nof people in America"},{"time":2026815,"text":"who agree with Steve Bannon,"},{"time":2030731,"text":"but they would never say it publicly,"},{"time":2032694,"text":"and so voting for Trump\ngave them the opportunity"},{"time":2035802,"text":"to agree with it silently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2038816,"text":"DB: On the issue of immigration,\nit's a legitimate point of view"},{"time":2043804,"text":"that we have too many immigrants\nin the country,"},{"time":2046255,"text":"that it's economically costly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2047745,"text":"CA: That we have too many --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2049125,"text":"DB: Immigrants in the country,\nespecially from Britain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2051758,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2052956,"text":"GC: I kind of like the British accent, OK?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2055730,"text":"CA: I apologize. America, I am sorry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2058101,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2059780,"text":"I'll go now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2061521,"text":"DB: But it became\nsort of impermissible to say that,"},{"time":2067469,"text":"because it was a sign that somehow\nyou must be a bigot of some sort."},{"time":2070938,"text":"So the political correctness\nwas not only cracking down on speech"},{"time":2074913,"text":"that we would all find\ncompletely offensive,"},{"time":2077160,"text":"it was cracking down on some speech\nthat was legitimate,"},{"time":2079966,"text":"and then it was turning speech\nand thought into action"},{"time":2084538,"text":"and treating it as a crime,"},{"time":2086622,"text":"and people getting fired\nand people thrown out of schools,"},{"time":2089566,"text":"and there were speech codes written."},{"time":2091332,"text":"Now there are these diversity teams,"},{"time":2093150,"text":"where if you say something\nthat somebody finds offensive,"},{"time":2095854,"text":"like, \"Smoking is really dangerous,\"\nyou can say \"You're insulting my group,\""},{"time":2099574,"text":"and the team from the administration\nwill come down into your dorm room"},{"time":2103136,"text":"and put thought police upon you."},{"time":2105701,"text":"And so there has been a genuine narrowing\nof what is permissible to say."},{"time":2110914,"text":"And some of it is legitimate."},{"time":2112806,"text":"There are certain words that there\nshould be some social sanction against,"},{"time":2118193,"text":"but some of it was used\nto enforce a political agenda."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2121191,"text":"CA: So is that a project"},{"time":2122428,"text":"you would urge on liberals,\nif you like -- progressives --"},{"time":2125432,"text":"to rethink the ground rules\naround political correctness"},{"time":2130373,"text":"and accept a little more\nuncomfortable language"},{"time":2136092,"text":"in certain circumstances?"},{"time":2138950,"text":"Can you see that being solved"},{"time":2140708,"text":"to an extent that others\nwon't be so offended?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2144935,"text":"DB: I mean, most American universities,\nespecially elite universities,"},{"time":2148283,"text":"are overwhelmingly on the left,"},{"time":2149840,"text":"and there's just an ease of temptation"},{"time":2151726,"text":"to use your overwhelming cultural power\nto try to enforce some sort of thought"},{"time":2155943,"text":"that you think is right\nand correct thought."},{"time":2158256,"text":"So, be a little more self-suspicious\nof, are we doing that?"},{"time":2161483,"text":"And second, my university,\nthe University of Chicago,"},{"time":2164983,"text":"sent out this letter saying,\nwe will have no safe spaces."},{"time":2167737,"text":"There will be no critique\nof micro-aggression."},{"time":2170171,"text":"If you get your feelings hurt,\nwell, welcome to the world of education."},{"time":2173656,"text":"I do think that policy --"},{"time":2175094,"text":"which is being embraced by a lot\nof people on the left, by the way --"},{"time":2178452,"text":"is just a corrective to what's happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2180642,"text":"CA: So here's a question\nfrom Karen Holloway:"},{"time":2182775,"text":"How do we foster an American culture"},{"time":2185129,"text":"that's forward-looking, like Hamilton,"},{"time":2187677,"text":"that expects and deals with change,"},{"time":2190229,"text":"rather than wanting to have everything\ngo back to some fictional past?"},{"time":2195104,"text":"That's an easy question, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2196706,"text":"GC: Well, I'm still a believer\nin the American dream,"},{"time":2199321,"text":"and I think what we can teach\nour children is the basics,"},{"time":2202779,"text":"which is that hard work"},{"time":2206200,"text":"and believing in yourself"},{"time":2209597,"text":"in America, you can achieve\nwhatever you want."},{"time":2211841,"text":"I was told that every single day."},{"time":2213526,"text":"When I got in the real world, I was like,\nwow, that's maybe not always so true."},{"time":2217581,"text":"But I still believe in that."},{"time":2219276,"text":"Maybe I'm being too optimistic."},{"time":2220873,"text":"So I still look towards the future\nfor that to continue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2225108,"text":"DB: I think you're being too optimistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2227294,"text":"GC: You do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2228476,"text":"DB: The odds of an American young person\nexceeding their parents' salary --"},{"time":2232532,"text":"a generation ago, like 86 percent did it."},{"time":2235093,"text":"Now 51 percent do it."},{"time":2236876,"text":"There's just been a problem\nin social mobility in the country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2240168,"text":"CA: You've written that this entire\ncentury has basically been a disaster,"},{"time":2245021,"text":"that the age of sunny growth is over\nand we're in deep trouble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2250678,"text":"DB: Yeah, I mean, we averaged,\nin real terms, population-adjusted,"},{"time":2255161,"text":"two or three percent growth for 50 years,"},{"time":2257305,"text":"and now we've had less\nthan one percent growth."},{"time":2259873,"text":"And so there's something seeping out."},{"time":2262396,"text":"And so if I'm going to tell people\nthat they should take risks,"},{"time":2266993,"text":"one of the things we're seeing\nis a rapid decline in mobility,"},{"time":2270064,"text":"the number of people who are moving\nacross state lines,"},{"time":2273457,"text":"and that's especially true\namong millennials."},{"time":2276496,"text":"It's young people that are moving less."},{"time":2278410,"text":"So how do we give people the security\nfrom which they can take risk?"},{"time":2282335,"text":"And I'm a big believer in attachment\ntheory of raising children,"},{"time":2285941,"text":"and attachment theory\nis based on the motto"},{"time":2288549,"text":"that all of life is a series\nof daring adventures from a secure base."},{"time":2293579,"text":"Have you parents given you a secure base?"},{"time":2295976,"text":"And as a society,\nwe do not have a secure base,"},{"time":2298373,"text":"and we won't get to that \"Hamilton,\"\nrisk-taking, energetic ethos"},{"time":2302785,"text":"until we can supply a secure base."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2305266,"text":"CA: So I wonder whether\nthere's ground here"},{"time":2308689,"text":"to create almost like a shared agenda,\na bridging conversation,"},{"time":2313470,"text":"on the one hand recognizing\nthat there is this really deep problem"},{"time":2318840,"text":"that the system,\nthe economic system that we built,"},{"time":2321369,"text":"seems to be misfiring right now."},{"time":2325244,"text":"Second, that maybe, if you're right\nthat it's not all about immigrants,"},{"time":2330638,"text":"it's probably more about technology,"},{"time":2332620,"text":"if you could win that argument,"},{"time":2334668,"text":"that de-emphasizes what seems to me\nthe single most divisive territory"},{"time":2339861,"text":"between Trump supporters and others,\nwhich is around the role of the other."},{"time":2343939,"text":"It's very offensive to people on the left\nto have the other demonized"},{"time":2348013,"text":"to the extent that the other\nseems to be demonized."},{"time":2350742,"text":"That feels deeply immoral,"},{"time":2353344,"text":"and maybe people on the left\ncould agree, as you said,"},{"time":2356238,"text":"that immigration\nmay have happened too fast,"},{"time":2359123,"text":"and there is a limit beyond which\nhuman societies struggle,"},{"time":2363724,"text":"but nonetheless this whole problem\nbecomes de-emphasized"},{"time":2367837,"text":"if automation is the key issue,"},{"time":2369996,"text":"and then we try to work together\non recognizing that it's real,"},{"time":2372974,"text":"recognizing that the problem\nprobably wasn't properly addressed"},{"time":2376127,"text":"or seen or heard,"},{"time":2377497,"text":"and try to figure out\nhow to rebuild communities"},{"time":2380830,"text":"using, well, using what?"},{"time":2382862,"text":"That seems to me to become\nthe fertile conversation of the future:"},{"time":2386922,"text":"How do we rebuild communities\nin this modern age,"},{"time":2390066,"text":"with technology doing what it's doing,"},{"time":2392422,"text":"and reimagine this bright future?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2394641,"text":"GC: That's why I go back to optimism."},{"time":2396768,"text":"I'm not being ... it's not like\nI'm not looking at the facts,"},{"time":2400667,"text":"where we've come or where we've come from."},{"time":2403129,"text":"But for gosh sakes, if we don't look\nat it from an optimistic point of view --"},{"time":2407140,"text":"I'm refusing to do that just yet."},{"time":2408868,"text":"I'm not raising my 12- and 13-year-old\nto say, \"Look, the world is dim.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":2413106,"text":"CA; We're going to have\none more question from the room here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2416126,"text":"Questioner: Hi. Hello. Sorry."},{"time":2419816,"text":"You both mentioned\nthe infrastructure plan and Russia"},{"time":2423344,"text":"and some other things that wouldn't be\ntraditional Republican priorities."},{"time":2428733,"text":"What do you think, or when,\nwill Republicans be motivated"},{"time":2435326,"text":"to take a stand against Trumpism?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2439739,"text":"GC: After last night, not for a while."},{"time":2442686,"text":"He changed a lot last night, I believe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2445060,"text":"DB: His popularity among Republicans --\nhe's got 85 percent approval,"},{"time":2448735,"text":"which is higher than Reagan\nhad at this time,"},{"time":2450979,"text":"and that's because society\nhas just gotten more polarized."},{"time":2453919,"text":"So people follow the party\nmuch more than they used to."},{"time":2456592,"text":"So if you're waiting for Paul Ryan\nand the Republicans in Congress"},{"time":2459772,"text":"to flake away,"},{"time":2460955,"text":"it's going to take a little while."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2462628,"text":"GC: But also because they're all\nconcerned about reelection,"},{"time":2466134,"text":"and Trump has so much power\nwith getting people either for you"},{"time":2469853,"text":"or against you,"},{"time":2471318,"text":"and so, they're vacillating\nevery day, probably:"},{"time":2473680,"text":"\"Well, should I go against\nor should I not?\""},{"time":2475820,"text":"But last night, where he finally\nsounded presidential,"},{"time":2479343,"text":"I think most Republicans are breathing\na sigh of relief today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2483099,"text":"DB: The half-life of that is short."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2485413,"text":"GC: Right -- I was just going to say,\nuntil Twitter happens again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2488692,"text":"CA: OK, I want to give\neach of you the chance"},{"time":2491784,"text":"to imagine you're speaking\nto -- I don't know --"},{"time":2495635,"text":"the people online who are watching this,"},{"time":2497610,"text":"who may be Trump supporters,"},{"time":2499180,"text":"who may be on the left,\nsomewhere in the middle."},{"time":2502829,"text":"How would you advise them to bridge\nor to relate to other people?"},{"time":2509648,"text":"Can you share any final wisdom on this?"},{"time":2513821,"text":"Or if you think that they shouldn't,\ntell them that as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2517619,"text":"GC: I would just start by saying"},{"time":2519279,"text":"that I really think any change\nand coming together starts from the top,"},{"time":2523614,"text":"just like any other organization."},{"time":2526714,"text":"And I would love if, somehow,"},{"time":2529616,"text":"Trump supporters or people on the left\ncould encourage their leaders"},{"time":2534203,"text":"to show that compassion from the top,"},{"time":2536779,"text":"because imagine the change\nthat we could have"},{"time":2540477,"text":"if Donald Trump tweeted out today,"},{"time":2542629,"text":"to all of his supporters,"},{"time":2544314,"text":"\"Let's not be vile anymore to each other."},{"time":2546998,"text":"Let's have more understanding."},{"time":2548696,"text":"As a leader, I'm going\nto be more inclusive"},{"time":2551550,"text":"to all of the people of America.\""},{"time":2554392,"text":"To me, it starts at the top."},{"time":2556509,"text":"Is he going to do that? I have no idea."},{"time":2559910,"text":"But I think that everything\nstarts from the top,"},{"time":2562634,"text":"and the power that he has"},{"time":2564387,"text":"in encouraging his supporters"},{"time":2567400,"text":"to have an understanding of where\npeople are coming from on the other side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2572497,"text":"CA: David. DB: Yeah, I guess I would say"},{"time":2575020,"text":"I don't think we can teach\neach other to be civil,"},{"time":2577786,"text":"and give us sermons on civility."},{"time":2579553,"text":"That's not going to do it."},{"time":2580821,"text":"It's substance and how we act,"},{"time":2582529,"text":"and the nice thing about Donald Trump\nis he smashed our categories."},{"time":2586172,"text":"All the categories that we thought\nwe were thinking in, they're obsolete."},{"time":2590318,"text":"They were great for the 20th century.\nThey're not good for today."},{"time":2593424,"text":"He's got an agenda which is about\nclosing borders and closing trade."},{"time":2596679,"text":"I just don't think it's going to work."},{"time":2598528,"text":"I think if we want to rebuild\ncommunities, recreate jobs,"},{"time":2601373,"text":"we need a different set of agenda"},{"time":2603051,"text":"that smashes through all our current\ndivisions and our current categories."},{"time":2606646,"text":"For me, that agenda is Reaganism\non macroeconomic policy,"},{"time":2610186,"text":"Sweden on welfare policy"},{"time":2612380,"text":"and cuts across right and left."},{"time":2614606,"text":"I think we have to have a dynamic\neconomy that creates growth."},{"time":2617567,"text":"That's the Reagan on economic policy."},{"time":2619424,"text":"But people have to have that secure base."},{"time":2621413,"text":"There have to be\nnurse-family partnerships;"},{"time":2623488,"text":"there has to be universal preschool;"},{"time":2625290,"text":"there have to be charter schools;"},{"time":2627309,"text":"there have to be college programs\nwith wraparound programs"},{"time":2630301,"text":"for parents and communities."},{"time":2631806,"text":"We need to help heal the crisis\nof social solidarity in this country"},{"time":2636826,"text":"and help heal families,"},{"time":2638346,"text":"and government just has to get\na lot more involved"},{"time":2640704,"text":"in the way liberals like\nto rebuild communities."},{"time":2644391,"text":"At the other hand, we have to have\nan economy that's free and open"},{"time":2647637,"text":"the way conservatives used to like."},{"time":2649587,"text":"And so getting the substance right\nis how you smash through"},{"time":2652669,"text":"the partisan identities,"},{"time":2654085,"text":"because the substance is what\nultimately shapes our polarization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2658752,"text":"CA: David and Gretchen, thank you so much"},{"time":2660745,"text":"for an absolutely\nfascinating conversation."},{"time":2662904,"text":"Thank you. That was really,\nreally interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2666065,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2669412,"text":"Hey, let's keep the conversation going."},{"time":2673704,"text":"We're continuing to try and figure out"},{"time":2675845,"text":"whether we can add something here,"},{"time":2677505,"text":"so keep the conversation\ngoing on Facebook."},{"time":2679570,"text":"Give us your thoughts from whatever part\nof the political spectrum you're on,"},{"time":2683284,"text":"and actually, wherever\nin the world you are."},{"time":2685369,"text":"This is not just about America.\nIt's about the world, too."},{"time":2689476,"text":"But we're not going\nto end today without music,"},{"time":2691834,"text":"because if we put music\nin every political conversation,"},{"time":2696650,"text":"the world would be\ncompletely different, frankly."},{"time":2699112,"text":"It just would."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2700914,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2703545,"text":"Up in Harlem, this extraordinary woman,"},{"time":2705659,"text":"Vy Higginsen, who's actually right here --"},{"time":2708108,"text":"let's get a shot of her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2709373,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2712766,"text":"She created this program\nthat brings teens together,"},{"time":2717073,"text":"teaches them the joy\nand the impact of gospel music,"},{"time":2720541,"text":"and hundreds of teens have gone\nthrough this program."},{"time":2724544,"text":"It's transformative for them."},{"time":2726087,"text":"The music they made, as you already heard,"},{"time":2728299,"text":"is extraordinary,"},{"time":2729629,"text":"and I can't think of a better way\nof ending this TED Dialogue"},{"time":2734027,"text":"than welcoming Vy Higginsen's\nGospel Choir from Harlem."},{"time":2737858,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2739059,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2758888,"text":"(Singing) Choir: O beautiful\nfor spacious skies"},{"time":2763546,"text":"For amber waves of grain"},{"time":2768502,"text":"For purple mountain majesties"},{"time":2773250,"text":"Above the fruited plain"},{"time":2777980,"text":"America!"},{"time":2782649,"text":"America!"},{"time":2787182,"text":"America!"},{"time":2790546,"text":"America!"},{"time":2796318,"text":"God shed his grace on thee"},{"time":2800994,"text":"And crown thy good with brotherhood"},{"time":2805433,"text":"From sea to shining sea"},{"time":2819648,"text":"From sea to shining sea"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2833417,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}